bugs.fix:
When building the prefix sums, always propagate the previous value for both dimensions and then apply the delta for the current command. For example:
```python
for i, ch in enumerate(s):
    row_prefix[i+1] = row_prefix[i]
    col_prefix[i+1] = col_prefix[i]
    if ch == 'U':
        row_prefix[i+1] -= 1
    elif ch == 'D':
        row_prefix[i+1] += 1
    elif ch == 'L':
        col_prefix[i+1] -= 1
    elif ch == 'R':
        col_prefix[i+1] += 1
```
This ensures that each prefix entry reflects the cumulative displacement in both axes.

